profile_positions.description:
1. Implementing the Annual Demilitarization Inspection/Verification Plan; ensuring that Inspection Teams are adequate to effectively conduct Article IV and V inspections;
2. Providing leadership and management of inspectors within the Cell; working with relevant units across the Technical Secretariat (TS) to ensure the retention of critical knowledge related to the conduct of Art. IV and V inspections;
3. Implementing a robust process for capturing lessons learned from all missions and ensuring lessons identified are addressed;
4. Identifying best practices on CW inspections and on relevant processes and technologies with a view to improving Article IV and V inspector’s training;
5. Working with the Head of CBCP Cell on INS efforts to support and enhance the International Co-operation and Assistance (ICA)Division’s ability to develop and implement Capacity Building activities with States Parties;
6. Guide and develop cell projects for the purpose of skill sets development/improvement, knowledge sharing and inspection quality control;
7. Leading the planning, preparation and implementation of the annual Article IV and V inspection budget;
8. Preparing the costing sheet for Demilitarization Inspection Cell sub-programme.
